{{ill|Nyakuichiōji|lt=Nyakuichiōji|ja|若一王子|en:draft|6=simple|7=User:Immanuelle/Nyakuichi Ouji}} (若一王子[[ja:若一王子]]) is a part of {{Ill|Kumano Gongen|simple|User:Immanuelle/Kumano Gongen|fr}}. Identified with {{ill|Amaterasu|lt=Amaterasu-ōmikami|ja|天照大神}}. Worshipped at {{ill|Nyakuichiōji Shrine|simple|User:Immanuelle/Nyakuichi Ouji Shrine|en:Draft|Nyakuichi_Ouji_Shrine|ja|若一王子神社}}
[[fr:User:Immanuelle/Nyakuichiōji]][[en:draft:Nyakuichiōji]]
'''Nyakuichioji''' is [[Kami|a deity]] in {{ill|10=ja|11=神仏習合|the syncretic Shinto-Buddhist sect}}. He is also called '''Nyakuoji''' .
{{ill|10=ja|11=熊野権現|The Twelve Kumano Gongen deities}} enshrined in {{ill|10=ja|11=熊野三山|the Kumano Sanzan}} are divided into Sansho Gongen, Gosho Oji, and Shisho Myojin, with Wakaichi Oji being the first of the Gosho Oji. Prince Wakai's original Buddha is {{ill|10=ja|11=十一面観音|the Eleven-Headed Kannon}}, who is identified with [[Amaterasu|Amaterasu Omikami]] or [[Ninigi-no-Mikoto]] . She is enshrined in the fourth shrine at {{ill|10=ja|11=熊野本宮大社|Kumano Hongu Taisha}} and {{ill|10=ja|11=熊野速玉大社|Kumano Hayatama Taisha}}, and in the fifth shrine at {{ill|10=ja|11=熊野那智大社|Kumano Nachi Taisha}} (both are now called " {{ill|10=ja|11=若宮|Wakamiya}}" and refer to Amaterasu Omikami).
As {{ill|10=ja|11=熊野三山|the belief in Kumano}} spread throughout Japan, {{ill|10=ja|11=熊野権現|Kumano Gongen|fr||en:draft}} were enshrined in various places, but in many cases only Wakaichi no Oji was enshrined. Following {{ill|10=ja|11=神仏分離|the separation of Shinto and Buddhism}} in [[Meiji period|the Meiji period]], many shrines changed "Wakaichi no Oji" to Amaterasu Omikami or Ninigi no Mikoto, but some shrines continue to worship him as "Wakaichi no Oji" as before.
* {{ill|10=ja|11=王子神社_(東京都北区)|Oji Shrine}} in [[Kita, Tokyo|Kita Ward]], [[Tokyo Metropolis|Tokyo]] . * Wakaichi Oji Shrine in Anjo City, Aichi Prefecture. * {{ill|Nyakuichiōji Shrine|simple|User:Immanuelle/Nyakuichi Ouji Shrine|en:Draft|Nyakuichi_Ouji_Shrine|ja|若一王子神社}} in {{ill|10=ja|11=大町市|Omachi City}}, [[Nagano Prefecture]] . The shrine is dedicated to Prince Wakaiichi, who is enshrined in the 5th hall of Nachi Taisha Shrine. * The shrine grove of {{ill|10=ja|11=若一王子神社 (藤枝市)|Wakaichioji Shrine}} in Wakaoji and Fujieda 5-chome, [[Fujieda, Shizuoka|Fujieda City]], [[Shizuoka Prefecture]] . * {{ill|10=ja|11=熊野若王子神社|Kumano Wakaoji Shrine}} in {{ill|10=ja|11=左京区|Wakaoji-cho}}, Sakyo Ward, [[Kyoto|Kyoto City]] . {{ill|10=ja|11=後白河天皇|Emperor Goshirakawa}} enshrined Kumano Gongen. It is also known as "Wakaoji Shrine" or "Wakaoji-san" <ref>{{Cite web|title=若王子神社|url=https://kyoto-design.jp/spot/3148|access-date=2019-12-19|website=KYOTO-design|publisher=k-iweb|和書}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|title=若王子神社|url=https://kotobank.jp/word/%E8%8B%A5%E7%8E%8B%E5%AD%90%E7%A5%9E%E7%A4%BE-110362|access-date=2019-12-19|website=コトバンク|publisher=朝日新聞社・VOYAGE MARKETING|和書}}</ref> . * {{ill|10=ja|11=若一神社|Wakai Shrine}} in Honmachi, {{ill|10=ja|11=七条通|Shichijo Goshonouchi}}, {{ill|10=ja|11=下京区|Shimogyo Ward}}, Kyoto City. This was the location of Taira {{ill|10=ja|11=平清盛|no Kiyomori's villa, Nishihachijodono}} [[西八条殿|.]] <ref>[https://ja.kyoto.travel/tourism/single02.php?category_id=7&tourism_id=438 若一神社].京都観光Navi (京都市観光協会)</ref> <ref>[http://kyoto.wakasa.jp/detail/25/1772/ 若一神社].ほっこり京都生活 (わかさ生活)</ref> * A shrine in {{ill|10=ja|11=田辺市|Tanabe City}} [[Wakayama Prefecture|, Wakayama Prefecture]] . It no longer exists, but a monument to "Wakaichi Oji Gongen" stands at the site. * The ancient name of {{ill|10=ja|11=周参見王子神社|Susami Oji Shrine}} in {{ill|10=ja|11=すさみ町|Susami Town}}, {{ill|10=ja|11=西牟婁郡|Nishimuro}} District, Wakayama Prefecture was "Wakaichi Oji Gongen Shrine." * {{ill|10=ja|11=熊野神社_(西宮市)|Kumano Shrine}} in Kumano-cho, [[Hyōgo Prefecture|Nishinomiya]] [[Nishinomiya, Hyōgo|City,]] Hyogo Prefecture was formerly known as Wakaoji Shrine. * The ancient name of {{ill|10=ja|11=平之荘神社|Hiranosho Shrine}} in {{ill|10=ja|11=平荘町|Hirasho-cho}}, [[Kakogawa, Hyōgo|Kakogawa City]], Hyogo Prefecture is "Hira no Sho Wakaichi Oji Gongen." * [[若一王子神社 (高松市)|Wakaicho Oji Shrine (Takamatsu City)]] - [[Takamatsu|Takamatsu City,]] [[Kagawa Prefecture]] * {{ill|10=ja|11=若一王子神社_(曽於市)|Wakaicho Oji Shrine (So City)}} - So City, [[Kagoshima Prefecture]]
