== Shrines == * {{ill|10=ja|11=王子神社_(東京都北区)|Ōji Shrine|en}} in [[Kita, Tokyo|Kita Ward]], [[Tokyo Metropolis|Tokyo]] . * Wakaichi Oji Shrine in Anjo City, Aichi Prefecture. * {{ill|Nyakuichiōji Shrine|simple|User:Immanuelle/Nyakuichi Ouji Shrine|en:Draft|Nyakuichi_Ouji_Shrine|ja|若一王子神社}} in {{ill|10=ja|11=大町市|Ōmachi, Nagano|lt=Ōmachi|4=en}}, [[Nagano Prefecture]] . The shrine is dedicated to Prince Wakaiichi, who is enshrined in the 5th hall of Nachi Taisha Shrine. * The shrine grove of {{ill|10=ja|11=若一王子神社 (藤枝市)|Wakaichioji Shrine}} in Wakaoji and Fujieda 5-chome, [[Fujieda, Shizuoka|Fujieda City]], [[Shizuoka Prefecture]] . * {{ill|10=ja|11=熊野若王子神社|Kumano Nyakuōji Shrine}} in {{ill|10=ja|11=左京区|Sakyō-ku, Kyoto|lt=Sakyō-ku|4=en}}, [[Kyoto|Kyoto City]] . {{ill|10=ja|11=後白河天皇|Emperor Go-Shirakawa|4=en}} enshrined Kumano Gongen. It is also known as "Wakaoji Shrine" or "Wakaoji-san" <ref>{{Cite web|title=若王子神社|url=https://kyoto-design.jp/spot/3148|access-date=2019-12-19|website=KYOTO-design|publisher=k-iweb|和書}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|title=若王子神社|url=https://kotobank.jp/word/%E8%8B%A5%E7%8E%8B%E5%AD%90%E7%A5%9E%E7%A4%BE-110362|access-date=2019-12-19|website=コトバンク|publisher=朝日新聞社・VOYAGE MARKETING|和書}}</ref> . * {{ill|10=ja|11=若一神社|Nyakuichi Shrine}} in Honmachi, {{ill|10=ja|11=七条通|Shichijō Street}}, {{ill|10=ja|11=下京区|Shimogyō-ku, Kyoto|lt=Shimogyō-ku}}, Kyoto City. This was the location of Taira {{ill|10=ja|11=平清盛|Taira no Kiyomori|4=en}}, Nishihachijodono [[西八条殿|.]] <ref>[https://ja.kyoto.travel/tourism/single02.php?category_id=7&tourism_id=438 若一神社].京都観光Navi (京都市観光協会)</ref> <ref>[http://kyoto.wakasa.jp/detail/25/1772/ 若一神社].ほっこり京都生活 (わかさ生活)</ref> * A shrine in {{ill|10=ja|11=田辺市|Tanabe, Wakayama|lt=Tanabe|4=en}} [[Wakayama Prefecture|, Wakayama Prefecture]] . It no longer exists, but a monument to "Nyakuichi Oji Gongen" stands at the site. * The ancient name of {{ill|10=ja|11=周参見王子神社|Susami-ōji Shrine}} in {{ill|10=ja|11=すさみ町|Susami, Wakayama|lt=Susami|4=en}}, {{ill|10=ja|11=西牟婁郡|Nishimuro District, Wakayama|4=en}} was "Nyakuichi Oji Gongen Shrine." * {{ill|10=ja|11=熊野神社_(西宮市)|Kumano Shrine}} in Kumano-cho, [[Hyōgo Prefecture|Nishinomiya]] [[Nishinomiya, Hyōgo|City,]] Hyogo Prefecture was formerly known as Nyakuoji Shrine. * The ancient name of {{ill|10=ja|11=平之荘神社|Heinosō-jinja}} in {{ill|10=ja|11=平荘町|Heisocho}}, [[Kakogawa, Hyōgo|Kakogawa City]], Hyogo Prefecture is "Hira no Sho Wakaichi Oji Gongen." * {{ill|10=ja|11=若一王子神社 (高松市)|Nyakuichi ōji-jinja (Takamatsu City)}} - [[Takamatsu|Takamatsu City,]] [[Kagawa Prefecture]] * {{ill|10=ja|11=若一王子神社_(曽於市)|Nyakuichi ōji-jinja (So City)}} - So City, [[Kagoshima Prefecture]]
