{{complex}}
{{ill|Nyakuichi Ōji|lt=Nyakuichi Ōji|ja|若一王子|en:draft|6=simple|7=User:Immanuelle/Nyakuichi Ouji}} (若一王子) is a syncretic Shinto-Buddhist deity and part of {{Interlanguage link|12=draft|Kumano Gongen|simple|User:Immanuelle/Kumano Gongen|fr}}. She is identified with {{ill|Amaterasu|lt=Amaterasu-ōmikami|ja|天照大神}}, and worshipped at {{ill|Nyakuichi Ōji Shrine|simple|User:Immanuelle/Nyakuichi Ōji Shrine|en:Draft|Nyakuichi_Ouji_Shrine|ja|若一王子神社}}
In the {{ill|10=ja|11=熊野三山|Kumano Sanzan}}, the Twelve Kumano Deities are divided into three groups: Sansho Gongen, Gosho Oji, and Shisho Myojin. Nyakuichi Ōji holds the premier position among the Gosho Oji. Nyakuichi Ōji’s Buddhist Prototype (本地仏) is the {{ill|10=ja|11=十一面観音|1=Ekādaśamukha|lt=Eleven-Headed Kannon}}, who is equated with [[Amaterasu|Amaterasu Ōmikami]] and [[Ninigi-no-Mikoto]]. This deity is enshrined in the fourth hall at both {{ill|10=ja|11=熊野本宮大社|Kumano Hongu Taisha|simple|User:Immanuelle/Kumano Hongu Taisha|en}} and {{ill|5=User:Immanuelle/Kumano Hayatama Taisha|6=en|10=ja|11=熊野速玉大社|Kumano Hayatama Taisha|4=simple}}, and in the fifth hall at {{ill|10=ja|11=熊野那智大社|Kumano Nachi Taisha|simple|User:Immanuelle/Kumano Nachi Taisha|en}}, all of which are currently referred to as "{{ill|10=ja|11=若宮|Wakamiya}}," symbolizing [[Amaterasu|Amaterasu Ōmikami]].
As the {{ill|10=ja|11=熊野三山|Kumano faith}} spread throughout Japan, {{ill|10=ja|11=熊野権現|Kumano Gongen|fr||en:draft}} shrines were established in various locations, often enshrining only Nyakuichi Ōji. Following the Meiji era {{ill|10=ja|11=神仏分離|separation of Shinto and Buddhism}}, many shrines shifted their focus from "Nyakuichi Ōji" to Amaterasu Ōmikami or Ninigi no Mikoto, though some continue to venerate him as "Nyakuichi Ōji" as before.
== Shrines == * {{ill|10=ja|11=王子神社_(東京都北区)|Ōji Shrine|en}} in [[Kita, Tokyo|Kita Ward]], [[Tokyo Metropolis|Tokyo]] . * Wakaichi Oji Shrine in Anjo City, Aichi Prefecture. * {{ill|Nyakuichi Ōji Shrine|simple|User:Immanuelle/Nyakuichi Ōji Shrine|en:Draft|Nyakuichi_Ouji_Shrine|ja|若一王子神社}} in {{ill|10=ja|11=大町市|Ōmachi, Nagano|lt=Ōmachi|4=en}}, [[Nagano Prefecture]] . The shrine is dedicated to Prince Wakaiichi, who is enshrined in the 5th hall of Nachi Taisha Shrine. * The shrine grove of {{ill|10=ja|11=若一王子神社 (藤枝市)|Wakaichioji Shrine}} in Wakaoji and Fujieda 5-chome, [[Fujieda, Shizuoka|Fujieda City]], [[Shizuoka Prefecture]] . * {{ill|10=ja|11=熊野若王子神社|Kumano Nyakuōji Shrine}} in {{ill|10=ja|11=左京区|Sakyō-ku, Kyoto|lt=Sakyō-ku|4=en}}, [[Kyoto|Kyoto City]] . {{ill|10=ja|11=後白河天皇|Emperor Go-Shirakawa|4=en}} enshrined Kumano Gongen. It is also known as "Wakaoji Shrine" or "Wakaoji-san" <ref>{{Cite web|title=若王子神社|url=https://kyoto-design.jp/spot/3148|access-date=2019-12-19|website=KYOTO-design|publisher=k-iweb|和書}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|title=若王子神社|url=https://kotobank.jp/word/%E8%8B%A5%E7%8E%8B%E5%AD%90%E7%A5%9E%E7%A4%BE-110362|access-date=2019-12-19|website=コトバンク|publisher=朝日新聞社・VOYAGE MARKETING|和書}}</ref> . * {{ill|10=ja|11=若一神社|Nyakuichi Shrine}} in Honmachi, {{ill|10=ja|11=七条通|Shichijō Street}}, {{ill|10=ja|11=下京区|Shimogyō-ku, Kyoto|lt=Shimogyō-ku}}, Kyoto City. This was the location of Taira {{ill|10=ja|11=Taira no Kiyomori|Taira no Kiyomori|4=en}}, Nishihachijodono [[西八条殿|.]] <ref>[https://ja.kyoto.travel/tourism/single02.php?Category_id=7&tourism_id=438 若一神社].京都観光Navi (京都市観光協会)</ref> <ref>[http://kyoto.wakasa.jp/detail/25/1772/ 若一神社].ほっこり京都生活 (わかさ生活)</ref> * A shrine in {{ill|10=ja|11=田辺市|Tanabe, Wakayama|lt=Tanabe|4=en}} [[Wakayama Prefecture|, Wakayama Prefecture]] . It no longer exists, but a monument to "Nyakuichi Oji Gongen" stands at the site. * The ancient name of {{ill|10=ja|11=周参見王子神社|Susami-ōji Shrine}} in {{ill|10=ja|11=すさみ町|Susami, Wakayama|lt=Susami|4=en}}, {{ill|10=ja|11=西牟婁郡|Nishimuro District, Wakayama|4=en}} was "Nyakuichi Oji Gongen Shrine." * {{ill|10=ja|11=熊野神社_(西宮市)|Kumano Shrine}} in Kumano-cho, [[Hyōgo Prefecture|Nishinomiya]] [[Nishinomiya, Hyōgo|City,]] Hyogo Prefecture was formerly known as Nyakuoji Shrine. * The ancient name of {{ill|10=ja|11=平之荘神社|Heinosō-jinja}} in {{ill|10=ja|11=平荘町|Heisocho}}, [[Kakogawa, Hyōgo|Kakogawa City]], Hyogo Prefecture is "Hira no Sho Wakaichi Oji Gongen." * {{ill|10=ja|11=若一王子神社 (高松市)|Nyakuichi Ōji Shrine (Takamatsu City)}} - [[Takamatsu|Takamatsu City,]] [[Kagawa Prefecture]] * {{ill|10=ja|11=若一王子神社_(曽於市)|Nyakuichi Ōji Shrine (So City)}} - So City, [[Kagoshima Prefecture]]
