e site. * The ancient name of {{ill|10=ja|11=周参見王子神社|Susami-ōji Shrine|12=draft}} in {{ill|10=ja|11=すさみ町|Susami, Wakayama|lt=Susami|4=en|12=draft}}, {{ill|10=ja|11=西牟婁郡|Nishimuro District, Wakayama|4=en|12=draft}} was "Nyakuichi Oji Gongen Shrine." * {{ill|10=ja|11=熊野神社_(西宮市)|Kumano Shrine|12=draft}} in Kumano-cho, [[Hyōgo Prefecture|Nishinomiya]] [[Nishinomiya, Hyōgo|City,]] Hyogo Prefecture was formerly known as Nyakuoji Shrine. * The ancient name of {{ill|10=ja|11=平之荘神社|Heinosō-jinja|12=draft}} in {{ill|10=ja|11=平荘町|Heisocho|12=draft}}, [[Kakogawa, Hyōgo|Kakogawa City]], Hyogo Prefecture is "Hira no Sho Wakaichi Oji Gongen." * {{ill|10=ja|11=若一王子神社 (高松市)|Nyakuichi Ōji Shrine (Takamatsu City)|12=draft}} - [[Takamatsu|Takamatsu City,]] [[Kagawa Prefecture]] * {{ill|10=ja|11=若一王子神社_(曽於市)|Nyakuichi Ōji Shrine (So City)|12=draft}} - So City, [[Kagoshima Prefecture]] == See Also ==
