hachijodono [[西八条殿|.]] <ref>[https://ja.kyoto.travel/tourism/single02.php?Category_id=7&tourism_id=438 若一神社].京都観光Navi (京都市観光協会)</ref> <ref>[http://kyoto.wakasa.jp/detail/25/1772/ 若一神社].ほっこり京都生活 (わかさ生活)</ref> * A shrine in [[:en:Tanabe, Wakayama|Tanabe]] [[:en:Wakayama Prefecture|, Wakayama Prefecture]] . It no longer exists, but a monument to "Nyakuichi Oji Gongen" stands at the site. * The ancient name of {{ill|10=ja|11=周参見王子神社|Susami-ōji Shrine|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/10=ja|qq=}} in [[:en:Susami, Wakayama|Susami]], [[:en:Nishimuro District, Wakayama|Nishimuro District, Wakayama]] was "Nyakuichi Oji Gongen Shrine." * {{ill|10=ja|11=熊野神社_(西宮市)|Kumano shrine|lt=Kumano shrine|lt=Kumano Shrine|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/10=ja|qq=}} in Kumano-cho, [[:en:Hyōgo Prefecture|Nishinomiya]] [[:en:Nishinomiya|City,]] Hyōgo Prefecture was formerly known as Nyakuoji Shrine. * The ancient name of {{ill|10=ja|11=平之荘神社|Heinosō-jinja|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/10=ja|qq=|1=Heinosō-jinja|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q22120257}} in {{ill|10=ja|11=平荘町|Heisocho|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/10=ja|qq=|1=Heisocho|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q17215850}}, [[:en:Kakogawa, Hyōgo|Kakogawa City]], Hyōgo Prefecture is "Hira no Sho Wakaichi Oji Gongen." * {{ill|10=ja|11=若一王子神社 (高松市)|Nyakuichi Ōji Shrine (Takamatsu City)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/10=ja|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} - [[:en:Takamatsu|Takamatsu City,]] [[:en:Kagawa Prefecture|Kagawa Prefecture]] * {{ill|10=ja|11=若一王子神社_(曽於市)|Nyakuichi Ōji Shrine (So City)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/10=ja|qq=}} - So City, [[:en:Kagoshima Prefecture|Kagoshima Prefecture]] == See Also ==
