As the {{ill|10=ja|11=熊野三山|Kumano faith|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/10=ja|qq=|comment=changed title based on wikidata|1=Kumano Sanzan|WD=Q10403700}} spread throughout Japan, {{ill|10=ja|11=熊野権現|Kumano Gongen|fr|en:draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/10=ja|qq=}} shrines were established in various locations, often enshrining only Nyakuichi Ōji. Following the Meiji era [[:en:Shinbutsu bunri|Separation of Shinto and Buddhism]], many shrines shifted their focus from "Nyakuichi Ōji" to Amaterasu Ōmikami or Ninigi no Mikoto, though some continue to venerate him as "Nyakuichi Ōji" as before.
== Shrines == * [[:en:Ōji Shrine|Ōji Shrine]] in [[:en:Kita, Tokyo|Kita Ward]], [[:en:Tokyo Metropolis|Tokyo]] . * Wakaichi Oji Shrine in Anjo City, Aichi Prefecture. * {{ill|Nyakuichi Ōji Shrine|simple|User:Immanuelle/Nyakuichi Ōji Shrine|en:Draft|Nyakuichi_Ouji_Shrine|ja|若一王子神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nyakuichi Ōji Shrine|qq=}} in [[:en:Ōmachi, Nagano|Ōmachi]], [[:en:Nagano Prefecture|Nagano Prefecture]] . The shrine is dedicated to Prince Wakaiichi, who is enshrined in the 5th hall of Nachi Taisha Shrine. * The shrine grove of {{ill|10=ja|11=若一王子神社 (藤枝市)|Wakaichioji Shrine|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/10=ja|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} in Wakaoji and Fujieda 5-chome, [[:en:Fujieda, Shizuoka|Fujieda City]], [[:en:Shizuoka Prefecture|Shizuoka Prefecture]] . * {{ill|10=ja|11=熊野若王子神社|Kumano Nyakuōji Shrine|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/10=ja|qq=}} in [[:en:Sakyō-ku, Kyoto|Sakyō-ku]], [[:en:Kyoto|Kyoto City]] . {{ill|10=ja|11=Emperor Go-Shirakawa|Emperor Go-Shirakawa|1=Emperor Go-Shirakawa|2=ja|3=後白河天皇|qid=Q317984|4=en|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/10=ja|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} enshrined Kumano Gongen. It is also known as "Wakaoji Shrine" or "Wakaoji-san" <ref>{{Cite web|title=若王子神社|url=https://kyoto-design.jp/spot/3148|access-date=2019-12-19|website=KYOTO-design|publisher=k-iweb|和書}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|title=若王子神社|url=https://kotobank.jp/word/%E8%8B%A5%E7%8E%8B%E5%AD%90%E7%A5%9E%E7%A4%BE-110362|access-date=2019-12-19|website=コトバンク|publisher=朝日新聞社・VOYAGE MARKETING|和書}}</ref> . * {{ill|10=ja|11=若一神社|Nyakuichi Shrine|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/10=ja|qq=}} in Honmachi, {{ill|10=ja|11=七条通|Shichijō Street|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/10=ja|qq=|1=Shichijō Street|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11353577}}, [[:en:Shimogyō-ku, Kyoto|Shimogyō-ku]], Kyoto City. This was the location of Taira {{ill|10=ja|11=Taira no Kiyomori|Taira no Kiyomori|4=en|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/10=ja|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, Nishihachijodono [[西八条殿|.]] <ref>[https://ja.kyoto.travel/tourism/single02.php?Category_id=7&tourism_id=438 若一神社].京都観光Navi (京都市観光協会)</ref> <ref>[http://kyoto.wakasa.jp/detail/25/1772/ 若一神社].ほっこり京都生活 (わかさ生活)</ref> * A shrine in [[:en:Tanabe, Wakayama|Tanabe]] [[:en:Wakayama Prefecture|, Wakayama Prefecture]] . It no longer exists, but a monument to "Nyakuichi Oji Gongen" stands at the site. * The ancient name of {{ill|10=ja|11=周参見王子神社|Susami-ōji Shrine|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/10=ja|qq=}} in [[:en:Susami, Wakayama|Susami]], [[:en:Nishimuro District, Wakayama|Nishimuro District, Wakayama]] was "Nyakuichi Oji Gongen Shrine." * {{ill|10=ja|11=熊野神社_(西宮市)|Kumano shrine|lt=Kumano shrine|lt=Kumano Shrine|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/10=ja|qq=}} in Kumano-cho, [[:en:Hyōgo Prefecture|Nishinomiya]] [[:en:Nishinomiya|City,]] Hyōgo Prefecture was formerly known as Nyakuoji Shrine. * The ancient name of {{ill|10=ja|11=平之荘神社|Heinosō-jinja|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/10=ja|qq=|1=Heinosō Shrine|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q22120257}} in {{ill|10=ja|11=平荘町|Heisocho|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/10=ja|qq=|1=Heisocho|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q17215850}}, [[:en:Kakogawa, Hyōgo|Kakogawa City]], Hyōgo Prefecture is "Hira no Sho Wakaichi Oji Gongen." * {{ill|10=ja|11=若一王子神社 (高松市)|Nyakuichi Ōji Shrine (Takamatsu City)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/10=ja|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} - [[:en:Takamatsu|Takamatsu City,]] [[:en:Kagawa Prefecture|Kagawa Prefecture]] * {{ill|10=ja|11=若一王子神社_(曽於市)|Nyakuichi Ōji Shrine (So City)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/10=ja|qq=}} - So City, [[:en:Kagoshima Prefecture|Kagoshima Prefecture]] == See Also ==
